INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '8e85c0fc-6c0d-4af7-bec6-2a4459059e51',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$LangChain + Hugging Face — Loading Hub Models as LLMs and Embeddings$escape$,
  $escape$LangChain integrates directly with Hugging Face via `HuggingFaceHub`, `HuggingFacePipeline`, and `HuggingFaceEmbeddings` — each targeting a different runtime context.

`HuggingFaceHub` hits the Inference API remotely, requiring only an API token. `HuggingFacePipeline` wraps a local `transformers` pipeline, giving you full control over device placement (`device=0` for GPU), quantization, and tokenizer kwargs — critical when the Hub's free tier rate-limits you.

For RAG pipelines, `HuggingFaceEmbeddings` wraps `sentence-transformers` models and slots directly into any `VectorStore`. The default model is `sentence-transformers/all-mpnet-base-v2`, but you can swap to `BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5` for a faster, smaller footprint with competitive MTEB scores.

Key gotcha: `HuggingFacePipeline` expects `task` to match the model's architecture — use `"text-generation"` for decoder-only models and `"text2text-generation"` for encoder-decoder (T5, FLAN). Mismatching silently produces garbage output. Always set `max_new_tokens` in `pipeline_kwargs`; the default truncates aggressively.$escape$,
  $escape$from transformers import pipeline
from langchain_community.llms import HuggingFacePipeline
from langchain_huggingface import HuggingFaceEmbeddings
from langchain_core.prompts import PromptTemplate
from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser

# Local LLM via transformers pipeline
hf_pipeline = pipeline(
    "text-generation",
    model="mistralai/Mistral-7B-Instruct-v0.2",
    device=0,
    max_new_tokens=256,
)
llm = HuggingFacePipeline(pipeline=hf_pipeline)

# Embeddings for RAG
embeddings = HuggingFaceEmbeddings(
    model_name="BAAI/bge-small-en-v1.5",
    model_kwargs={"device": "cuda"},
    encode_kwargs={"normalize_embeddings": True},
)

# Chain
prompt = PromptTemplate.from_template("Explain {topic} in one sentence.")
chain = prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()
print(chain.invoke({"topic": "tokenizer padding strategies"}))$escape$,
  $escape$python$escape$,
