INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '74278085-9aae-43f9-af5c-5bd141c96768',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$LangChain Fine-Tuning — When to Stop Prompt Engineering and Reach for LoRA$escape$,
  $escape$Fine-tuning in LangChain makes sense when few-shot prompting with `FewShotChatMessagePromptTemplate` stops scaling — typically when you need consistent output schema enforcement, domain-specific token distributions, or latency reduction from bloated prompts. Before reaching for LoRA, exhaust `ChatPromptTemplate` with detailed system messages and 5–10 curated examples. If `FewShotChatMessagePromptTemplate` hits 90%+ quality on 10 examples but degrades unpredictably at scale or adds 500+ tokens of overhead per call, fine-tuning is warranted.

When you do fine-tune, QLoRA (4-bit quantized LoRA) is the practical default — it fits a 7B model on a 24GB GPU with minimal accuracy loss. Load the result into LangChain via `HuggingFacePipeline`, wrapping a transformers pipeline with `BitsAndBytesConfig`. The fine-tuned model slots into any LCEL chain, `ConversationalRetrievalChain`, or tool-calling agent without API changes.

Choose full LoRA over QLoRA only when you need fp16 precision and have the VRAM budget. The 4-bit quantization loss is negligible for most NLP classification and extraction tasks, but measurable for math reasoning.$escape$,
  $escape$from transformers import AutoModelForCausalLM, AutoTokenizer, BitsAndBytesConfig, pipeline
from langchain_community.llms import HuggingFacePipeline
from langchain_core.output_parsers import StrOutputParser
import torch

bnb_config = BitsAndBytesConfig(load_in_4bit=True, bnb_4bit_compute_dtype=torch.float16)
model = AutoModelForCausalLM.from_pretrained("your-org/qlora-finetuned", quantization_config=bnb_config)
tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained("your-org/qlora-finetuned")

pipe = pipeline("text-generation", model=model, tokenizer=tokenizer, max_new_tokens=256)
llm = HuggingFacePipeline(pipeline=pipe)

# Slots into LCEL unchanged — no API surface changes from swapping base model
chain = prompt | llm | StrOutputParser()$escape$,
  $escape$python$escape$,
